1
00:00:05,505 --> 00:00:06,252
OK. I'm in.

2
00:00:06,339 --> 00:00:09,293
Agent Bristow works undercover
with her father, Jack Bristow,

3
00:00:09,384 --> 00:00:11,211
also a double agent with CIA.

4
00:00:11,302 --> 00:00:12,501
Get down.

5
00:00:12,595 --> 00:00:14,884
We'll have to learn to trust each other.

6
00:00:14,973 --> 00:00:17,262
Bristow's CIA contact: Michael Vaughn.

7
00:00:17,350 --> 00:00:19,224
My guardian angel.

8
00:00:19,310 --> 00:00:24,019
Her current assignment:
to infiltrate and destroy SD-6,

9
00:00:24,107 --> 00:00:27,440
a secret organisation
dealing in espionage, extortion,

10
00:00:27,527 --> 00:00:29,603
weapon sales, posing as the CIA.

11
00:00:29,696 --> 00:00:32,697
SD-6 has made over $400 million
in arms sales alone.

12
00:00:34,701 --> 00:00:38,864
The sanctity of this agency requires
the sacrifice of some personal freedoms.

13
00:00:38,955 --> 00:00:43,582
This is not about cutting off an arm of the
monster. This is about killing the monster.

14
00:00:43,668 --> 00:00:46,539
Bristow's mother:
formerly Russian intelligence,

15
00:00:46,629 --> 00:00:49,417
recently turned herself in to the CIA.

16
00:00:49,507 --> 00:00:51,132
Mom?

17
00:00:51,217 --> 00:00:56,508
Intel indicates she may still be
an enemy of the United States.

18
00:00:56,598 --> 00:01:01,426
The true loyalty of Agent Bristow's mother
remains unknown.

19
00:01:01,519 --> 00:01:02,717
Previously on <i>Alias:</i>

20
00:01:02,812 --> 00:01:06,596
The only way SD-6 will let you live
is if you destroy the life you've got.

21
00:01:06,691 --> 00:01:10,143
If you don't go public with this,
you'll be a dead man.

22
00:01:10,236 --> 00:01:12,443
I'm scared.

23
00:01:12,530 --> 00:01:14,606
I know.

24
00:01:18,411 --> 00:01:20,487
You ready?

25
00:01:26,670 --> 00:01:30,798
Are you suggesting that I kill my wife?

26
00:02:36,948 --> 00:02:40,151
Yeah? On my way.

27
00:02:49,794 --> 00:02:55,133
I'm Assistant Director Kendall.
I'm told you want to cooperate.

28
00:03:01,723 --> 00:03:04,890
Hey, Mr Bristow. Come on in.

29
00:03:06,561 --> 00:03:07,972
Let me ask you a question.

30
00:03:08,063 --> 00:03:11,017
Let's say you're hanging out
at your favourite neighbourhood restaurant,

31
00:03:11,107 --> 00:03:13,515
with some friends...

32
00:03:13,610 --> 00:03:19,730
Or whatever. You like to go there. You like
the food. What colour are the walls?

33
00:03:20,867 --> 00:03:23,903
I'm not really into interior decorating.

34
00:03:26,998 --> 00:03:29,074
I'll get Syd.

35
00:03:33,254 --> 00:03:35,924
Syd, your dad's here.

36
00:03:36,007 --> 00:03:38,498
OK. I'll be right out.

37
00:03:42,597 --> 00:03:44,886
You know, to the Vietnamese and Chinese,

38
00:03:44,974 --> 00:03:48,842
the colour white means death
and bad fortune.

39
00:03:49,354 --> 00:03:51,596
- Try red.
- Really?

40
00:03:51,690 --> 00:03:53,397
Hi.

41
00:03:54,526 --> 00:03:56,851
Will's sentencing is at two.
I'll meet you there?

42
00:03:56,945 --> 00:03:58,273
Yeah.

43
00:03:58,363 --> 00:04:03,488
Did you hear about Will? The story
he made up? He was high the whole time.

44
00:04:03,576 --> 00:04:05,949
Yes. I saw that on the news.
Unfortunate.

45
00:04:06,037 --> 00:04:08,528
You know what I wanna do to the guy
who introduced Will to heroin?

46
00:04:08,623 --> 00:04:10,165
I wanna kill him.

47
00:04:10,250 --> 00:04:14,330
- With my hands. I just wanna kill him.
- I can imagine.

48
00:04:14,421 --> 00:04:18,964
I'll see you at the courthouse.
And I'm gonna go buy some red paint.

49
00:04:25,223 --> 00:04:28,972
I thought you'd wanna know -
your mother's transfer is complete.

50
00:04:29,060 --> 00:04:32,476
She's being held at
a joint task force facility downtown.

51
00:04:32,564 --> 00:04:37,226
The idea that the CIA is willing
to work with Irina Derevko is insane.

52
00:04:37,318 --> 00:04:39,311
Worse - it's naive.

53
00:04:39,404 --> 00:04:44,908
Your mother didn't just conveniently turn
herself in. This is all part of a manipulation.

54
00:04:44,993 --> 00:04:48,362
Well, she's their problem now.
She's not yours.

55
00:04:48,455 --> 00:04:50,993
She's not mine.

56
00:04:52,542 --> 00:04:54,582
You OK?

57
00:04:56,171 --> 00:04:58,875
My shoulder's healing,
if that's what you mean.

58
00:04:58,965 --> 00:05:01,503
It's not, actually.

59
00:05:07,432 --> 00:05:09,674
Thanks for asking. I'm fine.

60
00:05:15,565 --> 00:05:18,483
I don't support the death penalty,

61
00:05:18,568 --> 00:05:22,067
but I hope that she dies
for all that she's done.

62
00:05:22,155 --> 00:05:24,646
I really do.

63
00:05:34,209 --> 00:05:38,253
Arvin Sloane is a man
of integrity and courage.

64
00:05:38,338 --> 00:05:43,166
As the head of SD-6,
he brilliantly executed Alliance policy -

65
00:05:44,052 --> 00:05:49,129
helping to slowly and invisibly
seize control of world markets,

66
00:05:49,224 --> 00:05:52,344
governments and technology.

67
00:05:52,435 --> 00:05:55,804
Now, as the newest
full partner of the Alliance,

68
00:05:55,897 --> 00:06:03,193
I feel confident that he will play a major part
in shaping that policy for years to come.

69
00:06:05,281 --> 00:06:11,534
I speak for everyone when I offer you my
condolences on the passing of your wife.

70
00:06:12,706 --> 00:06:13,452
Thank you.

71
00:06:13,540 --> 00:06:18,996
We respect and admire your willingness
to do what was necessary in that matter.

72
00:06:20,088 --> 00:06:24,382
You have been made aware
of the initiation procedure?

73
00:06:24,467 --> 00:06:26,294
I have.

74
00:06:26,386 --> 00:06:29,221
- And the reasons for it?
- Yes.

75
00:06:34,728 --> 00:06:37,563
Welcome to the Alliance.

76
00:06:41,568 --> 00:06:45,862
Sloane got back from London last night
a full partner of the Alliance.

77
00:06:45,947 --> 00:06:51,072
Emily knew the truth. Her death,
his immediately being let in?

78
00:06:51,161 --> 00:06:54,826
I am convinced
he killed his wife to get that seat.

79
00:06:54,914 --> 00:06:57,584
Killing his wife wouldn't surprise me.
Eating his wife wouldn't surprise me.

80
00:06:57,667 --> 00:07:00,337
SD-6 and the Alliance believe
that my mother is in hiding

81
00:07:00,420 --> 00:07:02,128
and they know that Khasinau's dead,

82
00:07:02,213 --> 00:07:05,832
and they are correct to assume that what's
left of her organisation is vulnerable.

83
00:07:05,925 --> 00:07:08,713
The Alliance wants whatever assets
they can get their hands on.

84
00:07:08,803 --> 00:07:15,767
- So where are they starting?
- My mother used blackmail extensively.

85
00:07:15,852 --> 00:07:21,143
In running her operation, she would get
dirt on people - powerful important people -

86
00:07:21,232 --> 00:07:24,186
and coerce them
into doing whatever she needed.

87
00:07:24,277 --> 00:07:26,317
Pornographic photographs,

88
00:07:26,404 --> 00:07:30,983
illegally obtained audio files, names, dates
- they're all on one computer disc.

89
00:07:31,076 --> 00:07:32,819
So what does the Alliance want? The dirt?

90
00:07:32,911 --> 00:07:37,039
To hear Sloane tell it,
it's all about God and country.

91
00:07:37,123 --> 00:07:39,910
It is our obligation to do whatever we can
to retrieve the disc.

92
00:07:40,001 --> 00:07:43,584
Now, what you're looking at
is the El Sebkba Hotel in Rabat.

93
00:07:43,672 --> 00:07:48,049
A Derevko operative named Mohammed
Naj lives and works out of the fourth floor.

94
00:07:48,134 --> 00:07:50,423
Early last week the blackmail disc
in question was taken

95
00:07:50,512 --> 00:07:52,054
to a vault at that location.

96
00:07:52,138 --> 00:07:57,215
The operation is simple - break into
the vault, retrieve the disc.

97
00:07:57,519 --> 00:07:58,550
My flight's at six.

98
00:07:58,645 --> 00:08:01,052
Well, we'll make contact
with a countermission no later than three.

99
00:08:01,147 --> 00:08:02,143
OK.

100
00:08:03,942 --> 00:08:06,267
- How's Weiss?
- He's still in the hospital.

101
00:08:06,361 --> 00:08:11,438
But the doctors say he's gonna be OK,
and until then, I've gotta feed his fish.

102
00:08:11,533 --> 00:08:14,403
Yeah? Yes. Let him through.

103
00:08:15,078 --> 00:08:16,738
- It's Kendall.
- What does he want?

104
00:08:16,830 --> 00:08:18,205
- I don't know.
- I don't trust him.

105
00:08:18,289 --> 00:08:19,949
- We have to hear him out.
- Hear him out? He arrested me.

106
00:08:20,041 --> 00:08:23,706
- He's in control of operation.
- He thought I was the devil.

107
00:08:23,795 --> 00:08:24,874
Mr Vaughn, Agent Bristow.

108
00:08:24,963 --> 00:08:26,338
Did you clear this meeting through Devlin?

109
00:08:26,423 --> 00:08:28,249
No. I'm sorry.

110
00:08:28,341 --> 00:08:30,630
I don't have time to go through channels.

111
00:08:30,719 --> 00:08:33,292
There's been an interesting development
regarding your mother.

112
00:08:33,388 --> 00:08:37,220
As you know she surrendered to the CIA
and claims to want to cooperate.

113
00:08:37,308 --> 00:08:40,594
So she's handed over her agency's
operations manual - the Bible?

114
00:08:40,687 --> 00:08:45,148
No. And she won't talk about it.
She won't talk to us about anything.

115
00:08:45,233 --> 00:08:47,309
Then as far as I'm concerned
that's the end of the story.

116
00:08:47,402 --> 00:08:49,691
Well, that's the interesting development.

117
00:08:49,779 --> 00:08:53,777
It seems that the only person
she's willing to talk to is you.

118
00:08:53,867 --> 00:08:56,868
- Then you're outta luck.
- I'm afraid you're gonna have to talk to her.

119
00:08:56,953 --> 00:08:59,574
- Excuse me, you can't compel Agent...
- That's exactly what I can do.

120
00:08:59,664 --> 00:09:00,364
Are we through?

121
00:09:00,457 --> 00:09:04,537
I don't have to remind you that this is
a matter of national security, do I?

122
00:09:04,627 --> 00:09:06,703
Yeah, we're through.

123
00:09:06,796 --> 00:09:10,082
I'll wait to hear from you.

124
00:09:14,637 --> 00:09:16,429
Just so we're clear, Mr Vaughn.

125
00:09:16,514 --> 00:09:22,019
I know all about your participation in
busting Bristow out of federal custody.

126
00:09:22,103 --> 00:09:23,514
Convince her to talk to her mother

127
00:09:23,605 --> 00:09:29,228
or face charges for obstructing justice
and harbouring a fugitive.

128
00:09:29,319 --> 00:09:33,399
Guess it's two-for-one day on blackmail.

129
00:10:07,148 --> 00:10:12,024
So, Mr Tippin, do you understand what
you're being accused of here today?

130
00:10:12,112 --> 00:10:15,646
- Yes, Your Honour, I do.
- Felony charge of heroin possession.

131
00:10:15,740 --> 00:10:19,192
Misdemeanour count of being under
the influence of a controlled substance.

132
00:10:19,285 --> 00:10:22,073
- How are you pleading?
- Guilty.

133
00:10:22,163 --> 00:10:24,535
Under Proposition 36,
you are to receive probation,

134
00:10:24,624 --> 00:10:28,752
and are hereby ordered to complete
a certified drug treatment programme.

135
00:10:28,837 --> 00:10:32,786
In addition, you must complete
100 hours of community service.

136
00:10:32,882 --> 00:10:37,425
Fail to meet any of these requirements
and you will serve time.

137
00:10:37,512 --> 00:10:38,757
It's a subvocal mike.

138
00:10:38,847 --> 00:10:41,682
With it we can hear what's going on
between you and Dixon at all times.

139
00:10:41,766 --> 00:10:46,013
And as soon as you can, I want you to go
radio silent with him so you and I can talk.

140
00:10:46,104 --> 00:10:48,061
- Call waiting for spies.
- Yeah.

141
00:10:48,148 --> 00:10:51,848
Now, the blackmail disc is
in a safe in Naj's suite on the fourth floor.

142
00:10:51,943 --> 00:10:55,193
As soon as you get it, you'll deliver it
to this man - Richard Schmidt.

143
00:10:55,280 --> 00:10:57,771
He's working under a diplomatic cover
at the Rabat embassy.

144
00:10:57,866 --> 00:11:00,902
He'll be waiting for you on the third floor.

145
00:11:00,994 --> 00:11:05,122
Now, Sloane is obviously looking for
something specific. We don't know what.

146
00:11:05,206 --> 00:11:07,365
Schmidt will scan the disc,
analyse what's on it,

147
00:11:07,459 --> 00:11:11,456
and spit up a bogus copy that's close
enough to the original to fool Sloane.

148
00:11:11,546 --> 00:11:14,630
That's the disc you'll deliver to SD-6.

149
00:11:14,716 --> 00:11:16,590
OK.

150
00:11:16,676 --> 00:11:18,550
Or...

151
00:11:19,846 --> 00:11:25,469
you could ask your mother
about the contents of the disc.

152
00:11:29,898 --> 00:11:33,812
Kendall must really be putting on
the pressure for you to ask me that.

153
00:11:33,902 --> 00:11:39,738
Yeah. He is. But I've been thinking about it
myself. Sydney, you're good at this.

154
00:11:39,824 --> 00:11:42,576
I mean, this is what you're trained for.
Compartmentalising your emotions -

155
00:11:42,660 --> 00:11:44,867
you do it on every mission,
you do it with Sloane.

156
00:11:44,954 --> 00:11:47,706
This isn't the same.

157
00:11:50,001 --> 00:11:54,793
Syd, I would never force you to do this.
I would never make this an official request.

158
00:11:54,881 --> 00:11:58,879
But I also know that what you want
more than anything is to destroy SD-6

159
00:11:58,968 --> 00:12:03,013
and bring an end to the Alliance, and if
she can help us, then why not use her?

160
00:12:03,098 --> 00:12:06,383
Because I can't.

161
00:12:06,476 --> 00:12:08,682
Because I won't.

162
00:12:10,814 --> 00:12:14,265
Maybe you could shut down with her,
I couldn't.

163
00:12:19,739 --> 00:12:22,444
I'll talk to you from Rabat.

164
00:12:22,534 --> 00:12:26,448
I spoke with Agent Bristow and she has
no intention of speaking with her mother.

165
00:12:26,538 --> 00:12:28,447
- Mr Vaughn...
- Yes, sir, I know, it's unacceptable.

166
00:12:28,540 --> 00:12:30,367
Let me remind you you're asking
a woman to go face to face...

167
00:12:30,458 --> 00:12:33,210
- You don't need to remind me of anything.
- With the woman who abandoned Sydney.

168
00:12:33,294 --> 00:12:35,287
I know the story and I know
that you have your own issues...

169
00:12:35,380 --> 00:12:37,871
- I have issues with her. So should you.
- I've read the reports.

170
00:12:37,966 --> 00:12:40,587
- Mr Kendall, Irina Derevko shot Sydney.
- Yes, she shot Sydney.

171
00:12:40,677 --> 00:12:42,136
Point-blank range.
She could have killed her.

172
00:12:42,220 --> 00:12:46,052
But didn't kill her. Did not.

173
00:12:48,226 --> 00:12:53,813
That woman, 48 hours ago, was 100 per
cent pure bad news, but now she's ours.

174
00:12:53,898 --> 00:12:58,893
And there is just a chance, Mr Vaughn,
that she has turned.

175
00:13:01,865 --> 00:13:05,234
When she got done with my father,

176
00:13:05,326 --> 00:13:09,739
he could only be identified
by his dental records.

177
00:13:11,207 --> 00:13:16,035
Yes. Nevertheless, she headed up
an organisation that controlled people

178
00:13:16,129 --> 00:13:20,506
who influence policy decisions
at NATO, the UN, the World Bank.

179
00:13:20,592 --> 00:13:24,590
Even with all our resources, the CIA
doesn't know the scope of her operation -

180
00:13:24,679 --> 00:13:27,301
the key players, their methods,
acquisitions, ambition.

181
00:13:27,390 --> 00:13:30,724
I can get her to talk.

182
00:13:30,810 --> 00:13:34,226
I don't want you to ask Sydney
to see her ever again.

183
00:13:35,231 --> 00:13:38,351
Well, I'm not gonna make that promise.

184
00:13:40,528 --> 00:13:43,732
You're not the easiest guy to work with,
are you?

185
00:13:43,823 --> 00:13:47,442
No. No, definitely not.

186
00:14:05,053 --> 00:14:07,970
- I have a 20 on Naj and his bodyguard.
- OK, I'm coming in.

187
00:14:08,056 --> 00:14:10,973
OK, Syd. We're on.

188
00:14:13,228 --> 00:14:16,928
- Syd, you close?
- I'm right behind you.

189
00:14:30,912 --> 00:14:33,284
- You know, you always do that.
- What?

190
00:14:33,373 --> 00:14:36,374
What you just did with your hair.
It's your thing.

191
00:14:36,459 --> 00:14:40,243
- I don't have a thing.
- It is. It's your thing.

192
00:14:43,800 --> 00:14:48,841
If the rest of the hotel is like this,
<i>sarà perfetto. </i>

193
00:14:48,930 --> 00:14:53,259
- And how may I help you?
- My name is Beatrice Cunelli.

194
00:14:53,351 --> 00:14:56,934
<i>Mio marito</i> Silvio and I
are in town for three months,

195
00:14:57,022 --> 00:15:02,264
while I recover from a <i>ridiculo</i> jet skiing
accident off the coast of Majorca.

196
00:15:02,360 --> 00:15:06,488
Presidente Travel Agency
booked us into the Derrahm,

197
00:15:06,573 --> 00:15:09,657
which turns out to be
<i>totalmente inaccetabile. </i>

198
00:15:09,743 --> 00:15:14,950
Now that I see this, I call Silvio and tell him
"Bring the bags right over."

199
00:15:15,040 --> 00:15:16,617
Your bags?

200
00:15:16,708 --> 00:15:20,159
<i>Comunque,</i> we were at
a cocktail party last night,

201
00:15:20,253 --> 00:15:24,630
and the consul general says
that he simply raves about this place.

202
00:15:24,716 --> 00:15:28,167
Naturally, I called
and booked a suite <i>immediamente. </i>

203
00:15:28,261 --> 00:15:33,884
There must be some mistake,
mademoiselle. We are completely full.

204
00:15:33,975 --> 00:15:37,593
Do me a favour, darling.
Check for me.

205
00:15:38,229 --> 00:15:40,851
Beatrice Cunelli.

206
00:15:41,524 --> 00:15:45,024
Yes. Of course.
But I'm pretty sure it's...

207
00:15:46,738 --> 00:15:51,151
- Reservation for Mr and Mrs Cunelli.
- I hope it's a room with a view.

208
00:15:59,834 --> 00:16:02,954
All right, Dixon, I've got the key
to Naj's suite. I'm on my way.

209
00:16:53,638 --> 00:16:59,012
We're interested in a computer disc
containing information used for blackmail.

210
00:16:59,102 --> 00:17:02,720
We believe you're familiar with this item.

211
00:17:09,154 --> 00:17:15,406
That's an implied question. I'll make it clear
for you. Are you familiar with this item?

212
00:17:26,171 --> 00:17:30,465
I know you wanna see your daughter. I can
guarantee you that is never gonna happen

213
00:17:30,550 --> 00:17:32,839
unless she knows you're cooperating.

214
00:17:32,927 --> 00:17:36,379
Prove yourself.
Give Sydney a reason to see you.

215
00:17:36,473 --> 00:17:38,549
Sydney?

216
00:17:39,684 --> 00:17:41,807
Interesting.

217
00:17:44,356 --> 00:17:48,602
Agent Bristow is in Rabat now,
seeking to recover the list.

218
00:17:48,693 --> 00:17:51,315
Is there anything she should know?

219
00:17:54,240 --> 00:17:57,775
Next to the safe there's a fire alarm.

220
00:17:59,037 --> 00:18:04,244
If you wanna protect her,
tell her to pull it first, then open the safe.

221
00:18:04,334 --> 00:18:06,042
Why?

222
00:18:06,670 --> 00:18:11,628
I've given you a gift,
and all you get from me is one.

223
00:18:15,804 --> 00:18:18,295
You look just like him.

224
00:18:24,813 --> 00:18:28,063
I'm through with the prisoner.

225
00:18:53,425 --> 00:18:55,168
To find the safe, you're gonna need this.

226
00:18:55,260 --> 00:18:58,047
Now, it looks like just
a normal metal detector.

