00:19:04,644 --> 00:19:08,689
Now, the safe is a Walderson. It's an
original. The craftsmanship is incredible,

229
00:19:08,773 --> 00:19:11,099
which, lucky for you,
the same can be said about this.

230
00:19:11,192 --> 00:19:14,442
You know those stethoscopes that outlaws
would use to rob banks back in the...

231
00:19:14,529 --> 00:19:16,403
You know, with the horses
and the guns and the ca...

232
00:19:16,489 --> 00:19:21,282
Well, I studied how those worked,
being a bit of an outlaw myself.

233
00:19:21,369 --> 00:19:23,528
Basically, this -
superamplified version of that.

234
00:19:23,621 --> 00:19:29,078
Now, you just place this over the dial -
this part right here - and you type in 793.

235
00:19:29,169 --> 00:19:32,502
793. That spells "Syd",
in case you forget. 793.

236
00:19:32,589 --> 00:19:35,162
Cos on a phone the numbers
and the letters... You know that.

237
00:19:35,258 --> 00:19:39,470
And, basically, this will do the rest for you.

238
00:19:43,600 --> 00:19:46,554
- I need to talk to Agent Bristow.
- She's now radio silent.

239
00:19:46,644 --> 00:19:49,266
If we try and communicate
her SD-6 partner could hear us.

240
00:19:49,356 --> 00:19:52,310
And if we don't,
she might trigger the alarm.

241
00:19:53,068 --> 00:19:55,274
The locking mechanism is a set of wheels.

242
00:19:55,362 --> 00:19:57,568
The trick is to line up each notch
on these wheels with contact points.

243
00:19:57,655 --> 00:20:01,867
Now, once each notch is lined up,
part of the combination will appear.

244
00:20:01,951 --> 00:20:04,621
Now, when they all line up,
the lock will open.

245
00:20:04,704 --> 00:20:08,536
- We're almost there. Going radio silent.
- Just be careful.

246
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:10,411
- Now.
- Freelancer. This is Boot Camp.

247
00:20:10,502 --> 00:20:12,708
- Do you copy?
- Go ahead, Boot Camp.

248
00:20:12,796 --> 00:20:15,465
Sydney, do not open the safe.

249
00:20:15,548 --> 00:20:19,214
- What?
- Is there a fire alarm on the wall?

250
00:20:22,764 --> 00:20:25,006
- Yes.
- OK. Listen to me. It's a fail-safe.

251
00:20:25,100 --> 00:20:28,469
Do not open the safe
until after you pull the alarm.

252
00:20:28,561 --> 00:20:31,479
We had no intel on a fail-safe.
Where'd you get this information?

253
00:20:31,564 --> 00:20:34,055
Vaughn spoke with your mother.
The intel came from her.

254
00:20:34,150 --> 00:20:35,810
It's her disc, she's familiar with the vault.

255
00:20:35,902 --> 00:20:38,903
If there's a fail-safe,
only she's gonna know.

256
00:20:38,988 --> 00:20:41,906
And what if there's not?
I'm just supposed to pull the fire alarm?

257
00:20:41,991 --> 00:20:44,613
Sydney, I know this sounds crazy,
but I think it's for real.

258
00:20:44,703 --> 00:20:46,825
Vaughn, she wants me dead.

259
00:20:46,913 --> 00:20:49,748
If that were true, Agent Bristow,
she would have killed you in Barcelona.

260
00:20:49,833 --> 00:20:51,493
Did you talk to my father about this?

261
00:20:51,584 --> 00:20:54,870
Two minutes ago on the phone while we
were waiting for you to go radio silent.

262
00:20:54,963 --> 00:20:57,205
- What did he say?
- Your dad?

263
00:20:57,298 --> 00:20:59,789
- The answer is no.
- All I'm asking is that you consider it.

264
00:20:59,884 --> 00:21:01,676
- Consider the source.
- I don't need to be lectured.

265
00:21:01,761 --> 00:21:04,383
- This woman is not to be trusted.
- Jack, listen to me.

266
00:21:04,472 --> 00:21:06,928
In no circumstances discuss this
with my daughter.

267
00:21:07,017 --> 00:21:10,717
I don't think your father can think clearly
where your mother's concerned.

268
00:21:10,812 --> 00:21:13,220
- And you can?
- I'm trying.

269
00:21:13,314 --> 00:21:15,106
She has nothing to gain by lying.

270
00:21:15,191 --> 00:21:17,896
Miss Bristow, I want you
to pull that fire alarm.

271
00:21:27,871 --> 00:21:28,950
Sydney.

272
00:21:30,040 --> 00:21:32,116
I'd do it.

273
00:21:41,343 --> 00:21:44,178
Agent Bristow, pull that alarm.

274
00:22:01,613 --> 00:22:03,522
See what I mean?

275
00:22:12,082 --> 00:22:15,451
Dixon, I've tripped some kind of alarm.
What do you see?

276
00:22:16,086 --> 00:22:20,333
Naj and his bodyguard are on their way up.

277
00:22:20,423 --> 00:22:23,590
Just look for the disc.
I'll handle Naj.

278
00:22:50,328 --> 00:22:52,321
This is Freelancer.
I've got the blackmail disc.

279
00:22:52,414 --> 00:22:53,742
What's your position, Freelancer?

280
00:22:53,832 --> 00:22:56,323
- Leaving the suite. Heading for the stairs.
- On my way.

281
00:22:56,418 --> 00:22:58,790
We got it.

282
00:23:05,385 --> 00:23:08,054
Do you have it?

283
00:23:09,014 --> 00:23:11,505
- Syd, do you have the disc?
- Yes.

284
00:23:11,599 --> 00:23:13,473
OK.

285
00:23:17,188 --> 00:23:19,181
- What happened? Did you get it?
- Negative.

286
00:23:19,274 --> 00:23:24,149
- What?
- I repeat: the disc was not transferred.

287
00:23:24,946 --> 00:23:29,323
The satellite feed is up.
Sloane wants the information asap.

288
00:23:29,409 --> 00:23:31,485
Good job, Syd.

289
00:23:38,251 --> 00:23:40,623
Alain? Arvin.

290
00:23:41,671 --> 00:23:47,507
Yeah. I thought you should know that SD-6
is in possession of the blackmail disc.

291
00:23:47,594 --> 00:23:50,548
Thank you.
And more good news.

292
00:23:50,638 --> 00:23:52,927
You know that gentleman we discussed?

293
00:23:53,016 --> 00:23:55,174
Peter Fordson.

294
00:23:55,268 --> 00:23:58,851
Well, we now have information on him.

295
00:23:58,938 --> 00:24:02,390
Photographs.

296
00:24:02,484 --> 00:24:04,144
No.

297
00:24:04,235 --> 00:24:06,477
Of his daughter.

298
00:24:06,571 --> 00:24:11,482
Apparently, he's willing to pay a high price
to keep them private.

299
00:24:11,576 --> 00:24:14,862
Well, if you saw them, you'd know why.

300
00:24:16,373 --> 00:24:19,409
I leave for Helsinki tonight.

301
00:24:19,501 --> 00:24:22,074
I'm seeing Fordson myself.

302
00:24:24,089 --> 00:24:27,006
I wanna talk to my mother.

303
00:24:27,092 --> 00:24:30,508
I hate her. I don't understand her.
I think she's a monster.

304
00:24:30,595 --> 00:24:33,762
But if she can help us bring an end
to SD-6, then what I think is irrelevant.

305
00:24:33,848 --> 00:24:35,888
I'm not so sure.

306
00:24:35,975 --> 00:24:37,351
- What?
- I've been thinking about it.

307
00:24:37,435 --> 00:24:39,511
- I'm not certain that's a good idea.
- Is this about my father?

308
00:24:39,604 --> 00:24:42,391
- He has a point.
- He can't think clearly about her.

309
00:24:42,482 --> 00:24:43,264
That woman has an agenda.

310
00:24:43,358 --> 00:24:44,982
- I screwed up.
- I wouldn't be so quick to trust her.

311
00:24:45,068 --> 00:24:46,692
- We don't know what she's after.
- If I'd listened to her,

312
00:24:46,778 --> 00:24:48,569
we'd have the disc right now.

313
00:24:48,655 --> 00:24:52,190
All I know is she offered good intel
and I didn't choose to use it.

314
00:24:52,283 --> 00:24:55,652
Now SD-6 has the blackmail disc.
We don't know what they want with it,

315
00:24:55,745 --> 00:24:58,782
but they've got it now and we don't,
and it's my fault.

316
00:24:58,873 --> 00:25:01,495
I know I'm the one who tried
to convince you to see your mother,

317
00:25:01,584 --> 00:25:04,918
to be unemotional with her.

318
00:25:05,005 --> 00:25:10,675
I thought I could do it, see her,
and be as cold-blooded as she is.

319
00:25:11,177 --> 00:25:15,045
It's hard to explain what it feels like...

320
00:25:16,850 --> 00:25:19,637
sitting across from her.

321
00:25:20,687 --> 00:25:25,396
What she did to my family,
to my father.

322
00:25:25,483 --> 00:25:30,311
But she's your mother, Sydney.
With all she's done, she is your mother.

323
00:25:33,074 --> 00:25:36,443
Vaughn, if you're worried about me...

324
00:25:38,955 --> 00:25:41,446
you don't need to be.

325
00:25:55,972 --> 00:25:59,258
I called you in to say thank you.

326
00:25:59,351 --> 00:26:02,387
We now have the disc,
and it's because of you.

327
00:26:02,479 --> 00:26:04,518
What was on it?

328
00:26:04,606 --> 00:26:07,975
Horrible things.
Private moments.

329
00:26:08,068 --> 00:26:13,691
The disc is a collection, a physical
manifestation, of human weakness.

330
00:26:13,782 --> 00:26:16,355
A tool that some people...

331
00:26:17,535 --> 00:26:22,162
that your mother used
to extract favours from those in power.

332
00:26:22,248 --> 00:26:27,623
Which, Sydney, is something
that I wanted to talk to you about.

333
00:26:30,048 --> 00:26:31,922
Your mother.

334
00:26:32,926 --> 00:26:36,710
- What about her?
- You saw her in Taipei?

335
00:26:36,805 --> 00:26:39,722
Yes.

336
00:26:39,808 --> 00:26:42,559
Well, I just...

337
00:26:44,312 --> 00:26:50,185
I just wanted to remind you that
I am here for you, if you ever need to talk.

338
00:26:53,321 --> 00:26:54,815
Thank you.

339
00:26:58,493 --> 00:27:00,865
I wanted to cut off my hand.

340
00:27:00,954 --> 00:27:02,946
Did he say anything else
about the blackmail disc?

341
00:27:03,039 --> 00:27:06,704
- Why the Alliance wanted it?
- No. I thought you'd have seen it.

342
00:27:06,793 --> 00:27:10,838
No. Sloane sent the disc
to Alliance headquarters in London.

343
00:27:10,922 --> 00:27:15,631
I'll see if I can find out whatever was on
the disc and why it was so important.

344
00:27:15,719 --> 00:27:18,292
How are you going to do that?

345
00:27:19,931 --> 00:27:22,339
I'll ask Mom.

346
00:27:25,270 --> 00:27:27,761
- You've agreed to see her.
- Yes.

347
00:27:27,856 --> 00:27:31,521
- Sydney, she is the enemy.
- And so is Sloane.

348
00:27:31,609 --> 00:27:34,776
And if the devil herself wants to help me
bring him down, fine by me.

349
00:27:34,863 --> 00:27:36,986
She has never been interested
in helping you.

350
00:27:37,073 --> 00:27:38,698
- She told me to pull the alarm.
- Yes.

351
00:27:38,783 --> 00:27:42,033
And for all you know
that could have made things worse.

352
00:27:42,120 --> 00:27:45,489
Sydney, you're smarter than this.

353
00:27:45,582 --> 00:27:48,785
Your mother wants you
to think she's your ally,

354
00:27:48,877 --> 00:27:52,328
that she can you help get what you want.
Her intel might even be accurate.

355
00:27:52,422 --> 00:27:54,711
Once. Twice.

356
00:27:55,800 --> 00:28:01,471
But the minute you start depending on her,
she will gut you.

357
00:28:15,904 --> 00:28:18,276
Will, what happened to your face?

358
00:28:18,365 --> 00:28:21,531
You know the one thing they don't tell you
about doing community service?

359
00:28:21,618 --> 00:28:24,821
- Sun block.
- Oh, buddy. How'd it go?

360
00:28:24,913 --> 00:28:27,368
Hanging out with a bunch
of fellow drug addicts?

361
00:28:27,457 --> 00:28:31,668
Picking up copies of the newspaper
I used to write for with a stick? Not good.

362
00:28:31,753 --> 00:28:37,791
Oh, I saw you at the gas station over on
National with some guy. Like, dark suit, 50.

363
00:28:40,387 --> 00:28:44,052
- That was the liquor licence guy.
- What? Wait a minute. Like a Mafia guy?

364
00:28:44,140 --> 00:28:46,014
- Yeah, kinda.
- Francie?

365
00:28:46,101 --> 00:28:48,473
It's gonna take six months
to get a legitimate liquor licence.

366
00:28:48,561 --> 00:28:50,601
So you're hanging out
with the Gambino crime family

367
00:28:50,689 --> 00:28:52,147
and you're giving me grief
about doing drugs?

368
00:28:52,232 --> 00:28:54,224
- It's so not the same thing.
- No, it's not.

369
00:28:54,317 --> 00:28:56,476
You're involved with organised crime.
It's totally different.

370
00:28:56,569 --> 00:28:58,776
You have no idea what it takes
to start a restaurant.

371
00:28:58,863 --> 00:29:02,149
I have to deal with contractors
and subcontractors and...

372
00:29:02,242 --> 00:29:04,318
I know. I know.
I used to work at the Metro desk.

373
00:29:04,411 --> 00:29:06,617
I wrote, like, two dozen pieces
on restaurants -

374
00:29:06,705 --> 00:29:08,863
Health Department, ratings,
code requirements...

375
00:29:08,957 --> 00:29:10,784
I just need a liquor licence.

376
00:29:10,875 --> 00:29:13,366
I know, what you need is someone
who knows how the system works,

377
00:29:13,461 --> 00:29:16,213
someone who can help you navigate.

378
00:29:16,297 --> 00:29:20,378
What you need is me -
you know, former drug addict reporter.

379
00:29:20,468 --> 00:29:23,588
And sometimes lobster impersonator.

380
00:29:24,931 --> 00:29:27,173
I'll help you out.

381
00:29:28,351 --> 00:29:30,260
To get to the facility
where your mother is being held,

382
00:29:30,353 --> 00:29:34,433
you'll go through a secret entrance. Start
at the southwest corner of Riverside Park.

383
00:29:34,524 --> 00:29:37,893
Head east until you pass a homeless man
sitting in front of a statue.

384
00:29:37,986 --> 00:29:42,197
He'll have a sign indicating he's a Vietnam
vet. He'll have a cup. Drop a coin in it.

385
00:29:42,282 --> 00:29:45,947
Freelancer requests covert entry.

386
00:29:48,163 --> 00:29:51,366
- Copy that. Routing her in.
- At Riverside turn left.

387
00:29:51,458 --> 00:29:56,796
The traffic cameras will identify if you're
being visually or electronically tracked.

388
00:30:02,469 --> 00:30:06,418
In the underpass beneath the 134 there's
an emergency phone. It's out of order.

389
00:30:06,514 --> 00:30:09,349
If it's ringing,
you've been cleared of all surveillance.

390
00:30:09,434 --> 00:30:13,301
This is a series of three-digit codes.
Memorise them. They rotate weekly.

391
00:30:13,396 --> 00:30:16,481
After the phone rings,
enter the appropriate code.

392
00:30:16,566 --> 00:30:18,772
In front of you there's
an industrial shipping container.

393
00:30:18,860 --> 00:30:21,778
On the backside, a door will unlock.

394
00:30:23,531 --> 00:30:27,114
You'll go down a steep set of stairs
through a series of checkpoints,

395
00:30:27,202 --> 00:30:31,069
and a quarter mile later
you'll be at the operations centre.

396
00:30:37,462 --> 00:30:39,870
Agent Bristow? Vicki Crane.

397
00:30:39,964 --> 00:30:42,040
Right this way.

398
00:30:46,388 --> 00:30:48,464
Mr Kendall.

399
00:30:49,557 --> 00:30:52,048
Glad you changed your mind.

400
00:32:08,511 --> 00:32:11,429
You didn't pull the alarm.

401
00:32:24,486 --> 00:32:27,403
I wouldn't have pulled it either.

402
00:32:32,285 --> 00:32:36,235
We need to know
who and what is on the disc.

403
00:32:41,086 --> 00:32:42,959
How's your shoulder?

404
00:32:44,839 --> 00:32:47,876
- The disc?
- Peter Fordson.

405
00:32:48,677 --> 00:32:50,799
- Who?
- Peter Fordson.

406
00:32:50,887 --> 00:32:56,094
He has a file on the disc.
He's the man SD-6 will go after first.

407
00:32:57,811 --> 00:32:59,684
Why?

408
00:33:00,647 --> 00:33:04,063
- One step at a time.
- I need to know why.

409
00:33:04,150 --> 00:33:07,685
No. You want to know why.
There is a difference.

410
00:33:07,779 --> 00:33:10,566
Go after Fordson.
Trust me.

411
00:33:12,909 --> 00:33:15,578
Why should I do that?

412
00:33:17,414 --> 00:33:20,249
Because I'm your mother.

413
00:33:44,691 --> 00:33:48,274
Here's what we know about Fordson.
He's based in Helsinki.

414
00:33:48,361 --> 00:33:50,318
A year ago his company contracted
with the Pentagon

415
00:33:50,405 --> 00:33:53,192
to manufacture a terahertz wave camera.

416
00:33:53,283 --> 00:33:56,403
Put in a satellite
they can see into NORAD undetected.

417
00:33:56,494 --> 00:33:58,202
Last month Fordson failed
to make delivery,

418
00:33:58,288 --> 00:33:59,782
complaining of production problems.

419
00:33:59,873 --> 00:34:03,573
Or produced the camera just fine
but planned on delivering it to your mother.

420
00:34:03,668 --> 00:34:05,328
So SD-6 wanted that disc

421
00:34:05,420 --> 00:34:07,911
so they could blackmail Fordson
into giving them the camera.

422
00:34:08,006 --> 00:34:11,256
Phillips, get the floor plans for the
Lasgrove building. Any intel we've got.

423
00:34:11,343 --> 00:34:14,712
Crane, I want a meeting
on op tech in one hour.

424
00:34:14,804 --> 00:34:19,715
You're going to Helsinki.
You're gonna get that camera.

425
00:34:22,187 --> 00:34:24,060
He's got great bedside manner, huh?

426
00:34:33,615 --> 00:34:36,402
The guards will be changing shifts
in two minutes.

427
00:34:36,493 --> 00:34:38,201
You should be in the lab
by the time they leave

428
00:34:38,286 --> 00:34:42,035
and have five minutes
before they get back.

429
00:34:45,710 --> 00:34:52,840
How could I forget the wonderful things
that keep me amused?

430
00:34:53,426 --> 00:34:59,928
How could I forget
to worship you each day?

431
00:35:01,393 --> 00:35:05,437
I remember somewhere in my soul

432
00:35:05,522 --> 00:35:08,273
Syd, Sloane's here.

433
00:35:10,777 --> 00:35:14,525
- He's after the camera too.
- You wanna call off the op?

434
00:35:14,614 --> 00:35:17,650
No. We go for it.

435
00:35:17,742 --> 00:35:21,076
- Are you sure?
- I just need a minute.

436
00:35:21,871 --> 00:35:25,371
Mr Fordson. Arvin Sloane.

437
00:35:25,458 --> 00:35:27,866
You Americans are persistent.

438
00:35:27,961 --> 00:35:31,460
I'm telling you on the phone our company's
not looking for new partners,

439
00:35:31,548 --> 00:35:33,671
and still you come all this way.

440
00:35:33,758 --> 00:35:37,008
- Syd, you ready?
- The handbrake won't lock into place.

441
00:35:37,095 --> 00:35:41,045
Why don't we talk about it
on the balcony? Shall we?

442
00:35:42,559 --> 00:35:44,682
Syd, he is headed right towards you.

443
00:35:44,769 --> 00:35:47,343
- I'm not ready yet.
- Well, you better get ready.

444
00:35:52,110 --> 00:35:54,648
Syd, he's gonna see you.

445
00:36:06,916 --> 00:36:09,205
I'm good. Thanks.

446
00:36:18,261 --> 00:36:20,835
I'm at 14.

447
00:36:20,930 --> 00:36:25,011
- Where's Sloane?
- With Fordson, putting on the squeeze.

448
00:36:26,770 --> 00:36:29,724
- This is your proposal?
- No.

449
00:36:29,814 --> 00:36:36,316
My proposal is that we go downstairs,
that you give me your T-wave camera

450
00:36:36,404 --> 00:36:40,272
and that I keep your daughter's
depravations our secret.

451
00:36:41,117 --> 00:36:44,949
Derevko's gone.
You work for me now.

452
00:36:45,038 --> 00:36:47,529
Let's not waste time.

453
00:37:27,539 --> 00:37:30,705
Sloane just left.
I repeat: he is on his way.

454
00:38:03,241 --> 00:38:05,317
Found it.

455
00:38:06,578 --> 00:38:09,365
Syd, only four more floors to go.

456
00:38:10,331 --> 00:38:13,083
Got it.

457
00:38:13,168 --> 00:38:16,003
Meet me at the extraction point.

458
00:39:00,423 --> 00:39:02,499
Let's go.

459
00:39:08,014 --> 00:39:11,099
This is where it was.
I'm telling you.

460
00:39:11,184 --> 00:39:14,683
Well, if it's not here, it's somewhere.

461
00:39:14,771 --> 00:39:18,389
I don't know.
I swear to God, I don't know.

462
00:39:24,114 --> 00:39:26,439
Just think about it.

463
00:39:28,118 --> 00:39:30,359
Where could it be?

464
00:39:39,796 --> 00:39:42,085
'Twas in another lifetime

465
00:39:42,173 --> 00:39:44,083
One of toil and blood

466
00:39:44,175 --> 00:39:48,636
When blackness was a virtue
and the road was full of mud

467
00:39:48,722 --> 00:39:53,015
I came in from the wilderness,
a creature void of form

468
00:39:53,101 --> 00:39:55,972
"Come in" she said
"I'll give you shelter from..."

469
00:39:56,062 --> 00:40:00,724
We're on the same side.
It's time you started acting like it.

470
00:40:06,448 --> 00:40:08,689
Agent Bristow. Hi.

471
00:40:08,783 --> 00:40:11,405
We had a briefing with Derevko
about T-wave technology,

472
00:40:11,494 --> 00:40:13,119
what she knows about how it works.

473
00:40:13,204 --> 00:40:15,612
Two hours, and your mother
didn't say a single word.

474
00:40:15,707 --> 00:40:19,621
- It's Vicki, right?
- Yeah. With an <i>i</i> - at the end.

475
00:40:20,086 --> 00:40:22,708
Vicki, I'm tired and I wanna go home.

476
00:40:23,673 --> 00:40:25,796
I don't mean to be rude
but if there's nothing else...

477
00:40:25,884 --> 00:40:28,209
Oh, no. I'm sorry.
There isn't, no.

478
00:40:28,303 --> 00:40:31,304
Except the one she did ask was

479
00:40:31,389 --> 00:40:35,553
if someone would pass along
her congratulations to you.

480
00:40:35,643 --> 00:40:40,638
She seemed really proud.
I hope you get some rest.

481
00:40:41,191 --> 00:40:46,185
"Come in" she said
"I'll give you shelter from the storm"

482
00:40:54,788 --> 00:40:58,832
I was burned out from exhaustion,
buried in the hail

483
00:40:58,917 --> 00:41:01,490
I wanna see the prisoner.

484
00:41:04,214 --> 00:41:07,583
Hunted like a crocodile,
ravaged in the corn

485
00:41:08,343 --> 00:41:13,337
"Come in" she said
"I'll give you shelter from the storm"

486
00:41:20,939 --> 00:41:24,771
Suddenly I turned around
and she was standing there

487
00:41:25,318 --> 00:41:29,945
Let's get something clear.
You are not my mother.

488
00:41:31,908 --> 00:41:34,743
My mother was Laura Bristow.

489
00:41:34,828 --> 00:41:39,039
Laura Bristow died in a car accident
21 years ago.

490
00:41:39,124 --> 00:41:45,127
You are a traitor and a prisoner
of the United States Government.

491
00:41:45,672 --> 00:41:47,748
Look at me.

492
00:41:51,845 --> 00:41:54,964
We will interact only when necessary.

493
00:41:55,056 --> 00:41:58,805
You will address me as Agent Bristow
and answer only the questions I ask.

494
00:41:58,893 --> 00:42:03,105
There will be no personal anecdotes,
no comments about my job performance,

495
00:42:03,189 --> 00:42:07,567
no condolences or congratulations.

496
00:42:09,612 --> 00:42:12,697
Do you understand me?

497
00:42:18,246 --> 00:42:20,951
Do you understand?

498
00:42:22,792 --> 00:42:24,666
Yes...

499
00:42:25,837 --> 00:42:28,245
Agent Bristow.

500
00:42:37,349 --> 00:42:41,761
I've heard newborn babies
wailing like a mourning dove

501
00:42:41,853 --> 00:42:45,851
And old men with broken teeth
stranded without love

502
00:42:45,940 --> 00:42:50,437
Do I understand your question, man,
is it hopeless and forlorn?

503
00:42:50,528 --> 00:42:55,523
"Come in" she said
"I'll give you shelter from the storm"


